{"author":{"id":"3d96f57266608371b099fb1929e447e30149f877f92c249a5587ceb0a6bc2786"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1507292028,"nonce":"FWJZcTrjD7ZYouAh4hPuXE8I7EY=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMzNDczNzc1MA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1505#issuecomment-334737750"},"message":"Hi,\n\nThe version that is used in my PC:\nmothur v.1.38.1\nLast updated: 8/9/2016\n\nFrom the wiki, they remove the large parameter in 1.38 version.\n\n```\nmothur \u003e count.seqs(help)                                                                                                                                                                                                              \nThe count.seqs aka. make.table command reads a name or shared file and outputs a .count_table file.  You may also provide a group with the names file to get the counts broken down by group.\nThe groups parameter allows you to indicate which groups you want to include in the counts, by default all groups in your groupfile are used.\nWhen you use the groups parameter and a sequence does not represent any sequences from the groups you specify it is not included in the .count.summary file.\nThe processors parameter allows you to specify the number of processors to use. The default is 1.\nThe count.seqs command should be in the following format: count.seqs(name=yourNameFile).\nExample count.seqs(name=amazon.names) or make.table(name=amazon.names).\nNote: No spaces between parameter labels (i.e. name), '=' and parameters (i.e.yourNameFile)\n\n```","files":null}]}